          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USATNL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The measurements were performed using",
                "the 10 MV FN tandem Van De Graaff accelerator at the",
                "Triangle Universities Nuclear Laboratory"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The bismuth targets were 0.9525mm in diameter and 1mm",
                "thick, while the thulium foils were the same diameter",
                "but 0.1 mm thick. The foils were stacked (Tm/Bi) and",
                "placed approx. 16 mm from the outer flange of the",
                "gas-cell assembly, with the thulium foil nearest the",
                "neutron production target. Following foils were used",
                "in measurement",
                "         Energy (MeV)    Bi(mg)     Tm(mg)",
                "         23.5+-0.105     0.7393     0.0681",
                "         24.9+-0.130     0.7436     0.0680",
                "         25.6+-0.133     0.7355     0.0670",
                "         26.5+-0.138     0.7416     0.0684",
                "         27.5+-0.142     0.7386     0.0688",
                "         28.5+-0.147     0.7393     0.0683",
                "         29.5+-0.156     0.6833     0.0695",
                "         30.5+-0.165     0.6833     0.0684"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "After irradiation, the foils were mounted in",
                "front of lead-shielded high-purity germanium (HPGe)",
                "detectors for gamma-ray counting for approx. 24 h. The",
                "bismuth foils were counted at 2.5 cm from the face of",
                "one HPGe detector, while the Tm foils were counted at",
                "5 cm on a separate, but nearly identical, HPGe",
                "detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Due to the long half-life of the reference",
                "reaction used (31.55 yr), the bismuth samples were",
                "returned to LANL and counted on the Compton",
                "suppressed dual-clover HPGe detector system, which",
                "has significantly higher efficiency than the other",
                "HPGe detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
